{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3949fe33-376c-4368-98f5-12bd33b21c7a","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nYou only need to keep `EnableMSTestRunner`, which tells MSTest to build as an MTP executable.\n\nHere's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Rt3yUyWxt9Z7qvR3HuYy7Y","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01MUSfWd1MAHKqiFmbNoJbx1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8e04dae23cea4a36b09b5243c94d6e82/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8e04dae23cea4a36b09b5243c94d6e82/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"51efa1d6-f7bf-43cf-821f-70ffac9f7526","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true. They want to know about native MTP support in .NET 10.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. The property was needed in .NET 9 and earlier to opt-in to the MTP integration. In .NET 10, this is the default behavior.\n\nSo they can remove `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` from their project file. The `EnableMSTestRunner` property is still needed as it configures MSTest to use the MTP runner.\n\n\n</current_rewritten_thinking>","outputTokens":514,"requestId":"4C24:1414DF:D8E1E8:10D420A:6A012A42"},"id":"3208e17b-198c-4c50-9b39-446805a77aaa","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:00:59.131Z","parentId":"7f3fe24a-a97d-4326-b1a9-caed9af498db"}
