{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"86903811-ff95-4981-8b62-ae27c2b95a5d","content":"**Summary:**\n\n| Property | Needed in .NET 10? | Why |\n|---|---|---|\n| `EnableMSTestRunner` | ✅ Yes | Builds MSTest as an MTP executable |\n| `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` | ❌ No | .NET 10's `dotnet test` talks to MTP natively — this was the .NET 9 opt-in bridge |\n\n`dotnet test` in .NET 10 communicates directly with MTP test executables, so the old VSTest-to-MTP bridging property is obsolete. Just run `dotnet test` as usual and it will work.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"51efa1d6-f7bf-43cf-821f-70ffac9f7526","outputTokens":157,"requestId":"4C1C:24E49D:D58F63:10A08CB:6A012A4A"},"id":"09508dfd-5934-49ea-afe3-d48c16107464","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:01:03.402Z","parentId":"e3b065c7-68d1-4412-9cf7-273b99bf723c"}
